<a name="327"><span style="display: none">Last call to Enter "Visit Me at CES!" 2012 Exhibitor Video Contest- Deadline Extended to November 4</span></a>
<br>

<div class="sub-content-header">Last call to Enter "Visit Me at CES!" 2012 Exhibitor Video Contest- Deadline Extended to November 4</div><br/>

<p><div>
	<img align="right" alt="" border="2" src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/clapboard2.jpeg" style="padding:5px;margin-left: 5px;" />This is the last call to enter the 2012 Exhibitor Video Contest- Visit Me at CES! You could win a month&rsquo;s worth of free promotion on the homepage of CESweb.org! You know why CES is one of the most important things your company does each year, and now you can tell everyone else!</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	Create a short video explaining why your company is exhibiting at 2012 CES and why attendees should visit your booth. Your video much be one minute or less and include your booth number. Help us generate momentum for 2012 CES while creating buzz for your own exhibit!</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	Five contest winners will be selected based on voting by the general public. The Exhibitor Video Contest voting and winners will be promoted through our attendee newsletter- CES Up to the Minute, CESweb.org and our social media outlets. Get more votes by getting your staff and clients involved as well!</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	All video entries are due by November 4, 2011. Enter today!&nbsp;</div>
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<a name="326"><span style="display: none">Get Free Registration for Your Guests Through November</span></a>
<br>

<div class="sub-content-header">Get Free Registration for Your Guests Through November</div><br/>

<p><div>
	Free registration for the 2012 show ended months ago, but as a CES exhibitor, you have the opportunity to offer your preferred guests and clients free registration up through the end of November 2011. Exhibitor invitations are one of the most cost effective methods of using the branding power of CES to promote your company&rsquo;s presence at CES.</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	For this month you can download a series of banner advertisements in different sizes. These banners can be incorporated into your website or electronic messages promoting your presence at CES. These banners will link to a special registration page that gives your guests free registration for November.</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	With free registration ending one month earlier this year, we know that some of your preferred clients might have missed out on this great opportunity. Be their saviour! Your customers will love getting free advance registration (or reduced-rate on-site registration), and they will love that it came directly from you.</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	Check out our Exhibitor Invitation page to learn how you can download yours today.</div>
</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<a name="328"><span style="display: none">Your Company Gets Noticed!</span></a>
<br>

<div class="sub-content-header">Your Company Gets Noticed!</div><br/>

<p><div>
	<img align="right" alt="" border="2" src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/FollowMe-PhoneCollage.jpeg" style="padding:5px;margin-left: 5px;" />Hundreds of CES attendees are downloading the official CES mobile app, Follow Me, every day!</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	Add your logo for $25, and include product literature for download by users -- before, during and after the tradeshow. Exhibitors who&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	include their logo, documents and place ads on the mobile app receive the lion&rsquo;s share of the hundreds of thousands of mobile app page views!</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	Far-reaching, cost-effective sponsorships and ad packages are available on the Follow Me mobile app that last for an entire year. Check out our sponsorship and ad package flyer for more information on how to promote your company and your products in this popular medium. Help to build an industry reference tool to where you can direct your potential customers all year long, whenever and wherever they are!</div>
</p>
