		<tr>
			<td>
				<p align="center">
					<img alt="Allison Fried" src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/News/Newsletter/AllisonFried.jpg" style="width: 92px; height: 122px; " /><br />
					<span class="smallText"><strong>Allison Fried</strong><br />
					Public Relations Specialist</span></p>
				<hr align="center" color="#999999" noshade="noshade" size="1" width="90%" />
				<p>
					<strong>Maximizing the 2012 International CES Media Machine</strong><br />
					by Allison Fried</p>
				<p>
					&nbsp;</p>
				<p>
					The 2012 International CES is just two months away and people are talking! Exhibitors, attendees and media are filling their appointment books, scheduling travel and starting the countdown. The world&rsquo;s largest consumer technology tradeshow is right around the corner, and with more 5,000 press and analysts packing their bags, you have to ask yourself, is your company ready?<br />
					<br />
					Press coverage is vital to the marketing strategy of any successful business. CES provides the optimal opportunity to generate media coverage of your company and its products, a value that CES exhibitors continually rank as one of their top reasons for attending the show.<br />
					<br />
					Our media attendees are a &ldquo;who&rsquo;s who&rdquo; of the global press, from the national TV news shows to the top newspapers, radio stations, wire services, trade publications and online outlets, including ABC, the Associated Press, BBC, CBS, CNET, CNBC, LA Times, NBC, New York Times, Wall Street Journal, Washington Post and so much more.<br />
					<br />
					There are plenty of ways for you to reach the media attending the 2012 International CES, and we are here to help. Make sure you check out our <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/pr/prKit.asp">2012 CES Exhibitor PR Kit</a>. It is an extremely helpful resource full of tips for hosting a press conference, drafting press releases, creating eye-catching press kits and learning other great PR tactics that grab the media&rsquo;s attention.<br />
					<br />
					Our media season officially kicks off on November 8 at the CES New York Press Preview in NYC. Held in conjunction with the CES Unveiled, this event offers press an insider view of the products that will both turn heads for the upcoming holiday season and make waves in January at CES. The media buzz continues on January 8th at CES Unveiled in Las Vegas, the official press event of International CES. This event draws more than 900 top-tier press who come for a sneak peak of what will debut on the CES show floor. If you want reach the media early &ndash; these are the places to do it!<br />
					<br />
					Another great way to get in touch with our 5,000+ media and analysts is to create a press kit for either of our two onsite press rooms, S229 in the South Hall Connector of the LVCC or Zeno 4601 on the 4th level of the Venetian. Exhibitor press kits housed in either of the CES press rooms must be paperless. There are a couple of ways you can do this; you can bring in either CD ROMs, USBs or post a URL along with a brief &frac12; page spec sheet. You may also want to consider posting your news online through our <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/news/exhibitorNews.asp">Online Media Center</a>, hosted by BusinessWire. Press kits are the media&rsquo;s one-stop resource to find out all they need to know about your company and products.<br />
					<br />
					Every year at the International CES, the CEA Communications team talks to thousands of reporters about hot products and new trends emerging at the show. If you want your product to be included in these talks, e-mail pictures and details about your hot new product to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:hotproducts@ce.org">hotproducts@ce.org</a> and <a href="mailto:afried@CE.org">afried@CE.org</a>. All embargos will be honored.<br />
					<br />
					Next, if you have a TV friendly product and are interested in having it shown on-air, CEA members should contact Jim Barry, our digital answer man, at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:bosjim@comcast.net">bosjim@comcast.net</a> and send a brief description of your product for consideration. Jim tours around the country in the weeks and months leading up to the International CES to showcase upcoming products and trends that people can expect to see at the show.<br />
					<br />
					Finally, help the media know why they should visit your booth! Submit a 30 second video about new products you&rsquo;ll be unveiling at the 2012 CES, and we will feature your video in the press section of CESweb.org. Keep it brief and newsworthy, with info on booth location and new product news. Videos should be sent to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:PRcontacts@ce.org">PRcontacts@ce.org</a> by December 22, 2011.<br />
					<br />
					Another fantastic tool we offer is the option for you to download and use the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/pr/default.asp">CES pre-registered media list</a> (available December 1, 2011). The pre-registered media list contains contact information for all media that have registered for the 2012 International CES. It is the perfect way to target select media that are interested in covering your company&rsquo;s product category.<br />
					<br />
					And yes there is still time for you to schedule a press event. Companies who have major news to announce are encouraged to hold a press conference at CES. Each exhibitor is eligible to reserve one of our CES press conference rooms for free on a first come first serve basis. If you would like to take advantage of this option, please fill out our&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/docs/Sec5_Press_Conference_Request.pdf">Press Conference Reservation Request Form</a> and fax it to me a 703-907-7690.<br />
					<br />
					Tell your story to the local media. To gain more regional coverage, participate in the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/docs/Sec2_Things_to_Take_Advantage_of.pdf">CES Regional Media Outreach Campaign</a> and submit a quote from a company executive to be included in a press release sent to the media in your area. The deadline to participate in November 21, 2011.<br />
					<br />
					Finally, at this year&rsquo;s 2012 CES, you&rsquo;ll encounter an integrated social media experience! We encourage you to visit, follow, like, view and browse our social media platforms in order to get updates as they happen.<br />
					<br />
					Share your SM platforms with us so that we can identify you as a CES exhibitor in the social space. Furthermore, there&rsquo;s a great (and free) way to build excitement for your exhibit before you even get to Vegas. Exhibitors are welcome, and encouraged, to submit a guest blog post(s) for our official blog: <a href="http://blog.ce.org/">Digital Dialogue</a>. There are many ways to express yourself and company in a blog including words, photos and videos. Your blog post can feature your company, products and services but only in an informative way &ndash; no straight sales pitches, please! Make sure to specifically visit the social media portion of our Exhibitor PR Kit for example blog, Facebook and Twitter posts.<br />
					<br />
					These are just a few helpful hints for reaching the CES media machine and maximizing your company&rsquo;s media exposure at the 2012 International CES. Please feel free to contact me directly with any PR questions: <a href="mailto:afried@CE.org">afried@CE.org</a>.<br />
					<br />
					Sincerely,<br />
					<br />
					Allie Fried</p>
